[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man killed in dumper truck accident in Edinburgh

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been killed after being hit and crushed by a dumper truck in Edinburgh.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 55-year-old man was knocked down at about 09:50 at an industrial site in Dryden Street.
The man sustained serious injuries and was later pronounced dead at the scene.
A Health and Safety Executive spokeswoman said they were aware of the incident and were liaising with police.
